translated: Lindbeck, Torsten Salomon, civil engineer, captain, Linköping, b. 28/2/91 in Alnö, Västern. 1st child of forest administrator Gustaf L. and Louise Petterson. m. 27 with Ingrid Calais-Bärnheim. Children: Gun- born 38, Eva 30, Sven 32, Göran 33, Gunilla 36, Lars 44. - Studied in Sundsvall 09, Royal Institute of Technology (VoV) 10-14. Assistant engineer in the upper northern road and water construction district 14-17, designer at the water authority 17-18, also a surveyor for the canal commission 18-20, assistant engineer in the lower northern road and water construction district 20-23, engineer at A-B Övre Norrl. Ingibyrà in Umeå 23-24, assistant engineer and acting head engineer at the road and water construction authority 24-29, acting district engineer in the eastern road and water construction district 29-30, road engineer in Östergötland county 30-47, currently serving at the road and water construction authority since 47. Lieutenant in the National Reserve Officer Training Corps (VVK) 18, captain 26. Study trips to Germany, Switzerland, and Italy in 23, Germany, and France in 25. Royal Order of Vasa (RVO).
